channel.title: What is with the downloadable server!?!?!?
channel.description: :eek: ok I am very annoyed! well first let me start out with my info. I have a microsoft windows computer, made by dell, I have the appropriate java program to run moparscape, I KNOW I am downloading version 3.2, and my computer is NOT dead slow. Now to the good (or for my case bad :() part when ever I try to run moparscape (I have it fully downloaded, fully extracted and in its own folder) it does pop up, but then it just loads up to an average of 5% every time, and then exits out. I dont know what is happening, and I REALLY want to play moparscape! I know its not an error so if anybody can PLEASE help me I would REALLY appreciate it. thank you! oh, and when I try to run the online servers it shows the java symbol then turns all greyish-white with a little x on a piece of parchment up at the top-left corner. I dont know whether its a problem with my computer or the program its self :confused: so PLEASE people im BEGGING you PLEASE help me if you can! THANK YOU ONCE AGAIN. :confused: :| :confused: :| :confused: :| :eek:
